{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34074459-e1e5-4db1-910c-360c3b3b5312","content":"Here's the recommended MSTest setup:\n\n## 1. Project File (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles the test framework, runner, and analyzers automatically. No explicit `PackageReference` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable Parallel Execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `.runsettings` file at the solution root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>  <!-- 0 = use all available processors -->\n      <Scope>ClassLevel</Scope>\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr skip the file and add the assembly-level attribute in a single `.cs` file:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run Database Tests Sequentially\n\nApply `[DoNotParallelize]` to your integration test class:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Test_InsertRecord() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Test_ReadRecord() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll classes run in parallel **except** those marked `[DoNotParallelize]`, which run alone after parallel execution completes.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** `MSTest.Sdk` gives you a zero-boilerplate project file. Use `[assembly: Parallelize(...)]` for default parallelism and `[DoNotParallelize]` on classes that need isolation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a99df1e7-0acd-42b4-afa5-16f4802da588","outputTokens":475,"requestId":"5810:214BB8:5C0EE49:63FFB91:6A033949"},"id":"d5a04e9b-21b5-4515-8f5c-e7f26e63eace","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:46.159Z","parentId":"2873db2b-418a-418f-90f0-ae4de6434e66"}
